cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.CR

This paper discusses cardinality estimation algorithms in computer networks, specifically for counting the number of distinct flows. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning, which suggests it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper deals with data processing and optimization, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
